QUESTIONS: Does a 90 - 95% substance reduction rate mean that Ploom X is safer than cigarettes?

90-95% reduction on average in 9 toxic substances¹.
 Ploom X is [our latest / an innovative²] heated tobacco product which we believe has strong potential as a reduced-risk product compared to smoking cigarettes. QUESTIONS: Can you take Ploom X on a plane?
ANSWERS:
If you're wondering which heated tobacco products you can carry on a plane, it's best to check with your airline. 
  
 According to international flight regulations, you shouldn't put heated tobacco products like Ploom X in your checked luggage (the suitcase that goes in the hold). 
  
 Some airlines might let you take Ploom X in your carry-on bag, but you won't be able to smoke on a plane or use Ploom X while you're on board.
 
 You should also check the legality of Ploom X in the country to which you are travelling. Find out more about where you can use heated tobacco on our blog. [insert link to ARTICLE #3: WHERE CAN I USE HEATED TOBACCO (STREAM 2)]

ANSWERS:
Yes - but this depends on where you're travelling to. 
  
  Each country has different laws and regulations when it comes to heated tobacco, so it's a good idea to check in advance. You can ask the embassy for the country you'll be travelling to before you take your Ploom abroad. It's also a good idea to check and see if sticks for Ploom are available for purchase in your destination so you know whether you'll need to bring extra refill packs with you. Finally, if you charge Ploom with a wall adaptor, check to see if it is compatible with your destination. Charging via USB cable can be done anywhere in the world.
  
  To find out more about travelling with Ploom, have a look at our FAQ. [insert link to FAQ: Can you take Ploom on a plane?']

QUESTIONS: How do I clean Ploom S?
ANSWERS:
Cleaning Ploom S is really easy. Here's how to clean Ploom S using the Ploom cleaning tool: 
 
 1. Make sure Ploom S is switched off, and disconnected from the charger. 
 2. If you've just used Ploom S, wait until it has cooled down. Be careful - Ploom S can be hot just after you've used it. 
 3. Insert the Ploom S cleaning tool and turn it a couple of times - this should do the job. If you're wondering how often to clean Ploom S, we'd recommend checking to see if there's any residue every time you finish a pack of [brand] tobacco sticks. 
 
 To find out more, watch our video [Insert link to how to clean video].

QUESTIONS: How do I charge Ploom S?
ANSWERS:
It's really easy. Here's how to charge Ploom S: 
 
 1. Plug your Ploom device in using the USB cable provided with the device. 
 2. If your battery's empty, it'll be fully charged in around 90 minutes. 
 3. You'll be able to see your charging progress on the LED display. Once it's fully lit up, it means your Ploom device is almost ready. 
 4. When your Ploom device is fully charged and ready to go, the LED will turn off. If you're wondering how often to charge Ploom S, we recommend giving it a charge every x sessions. To find out more, watch our video on [how to charge Ploom S]. [Link to How to charge video]

QUESTIONS: How do I use Ploom S?
ANSWERS:
Here's how to use Ploom S: 
 
 1. Open Ploom S's sliding cover and insert a tobacco stick. Make sure the filter is facing upwards, and the ventilation holes are aligned with the top of your Ploom S. 
 2. When you're ready to start heating your tobacco up, press and hold the button until Ploom S vibrates. 
 3. If you want to use Ploom S in Quick Heating mode, release the button after the first vibration. If you want to use Ploom S in Intense Heating mode, wait until after the second vibration. 
 4. You can check your heating progress using the LED lights - once all the lights are lit up and Ploom S vibrates again, it's ready to go. 
 5. Once the heating cycle is almost finished, you'll feel a short vibration. And once the session is complete, you'll feel a long vibration and the lights will go out. 
 6. Take out your used tobacco stick - but be careful, it might be hot. You can put it in a stick tray until it cools down. 
 To find out more, watch our video on how to use Ploom S. [Insert link to how to use video]

QUESTIONS: When I switch Ploom S on, how long before it's ready to use?
ANSWERS:
It depends on the heating mode you choose.
  
 If you're ready to start using Ploom S, here's what to expect for your Ploom S waiting time:
  
 Quick mode - 20 seconds
 If you want to start your session up quickly, insert a tobacco stick, then press and hold the button until you feel the first vibration feedback. Ploom S should heat up in around 20 seconds. 
  
 Intense mode - 50 seconds
 If you want an intense taste and aroma, insert a tobacco stick, then press and hold the button until you feel the second vibration feedback. In Intense mode, Ploom S will heat up in around 50 seconds. 
  
 In both heating modes, you'll be able to check if Ploom S is ready using the LED lights. Once all the lights are lit up and Ploom S vibrates again, it's ready to go.

QUESTIONS: How do I switch off my Ploom S?
ANSWERS:
It's easy to finish using Ploom S.
  
 If you're ready to start turning off Ploom S, all you have to do is take out your tobacco stick, and then close the sliding cover. Closing the sliding cover is really important, because that's what stops the heating. If you don't do this, Ploom S will carry on heating until the end of the session (which is a max of 5 minutes).
  
 Be careful - if you've just finished a session, your tobacco stick might be very hot. It's a good idea to put your used tobacco stick in a stick tray until it cools down.

QUESTIONS: How do I set up the Ploom X manual lock?
ANSWERS:
You can lock Ploom X with a password made up of button presses and slider movements - so only you can unlock it. 
 
 Here's how to set it up:
 
 1. Connect Ploom X to power.
 2. Open and close the cover.
 3. Then, press the button until Ploom X vibrates.
 4. The light will flash for around 20 seconds. While it's flashing, create a short sequence of button presses and/or slider movements. You can use a minimum of 3 and a maximum of 10 movements. This will be your password.
 5. Open the cover and close it again. Your password is all set up. 
 
 To find out more about locking Ploom X, watch our video [Insert link to How to lock]

QUESTIONS: What's the difference between a heated tobacco stick and a cigarette or cigar?
ANSWERS:
Cigars, cigarettes, and heated tobacco products all contain real tobacco. 
 
 The difference is in how they are used. With cigarettes and cigars the tobacco is burnt, but with heated tobacco products, like Ploom, the tobacco is heated instead. This means heated tobacco products provide you with a smokeless tobacco experience.
 
 Ploom X is an easy, convenient heated tobacco product that uses innovative HeatFlow technology to heat tobacco sticks from the outside, giving you an exceptional tobacco taste sensation with no smoke and less tobacco smoke smell ¹.
 
 If you're using Ploom X, you'll need to use [BRAND] tobacco sticks to enjoy your heated tobacco experience.
 
 You can't smoke [BRAND] tobacco sticks the way you would smoke a conventional cigarette - and you won't be able to use a cigar or cigarette with Ploom X, either. You can read more about smoking alternatives on our blog. [Insert link to smoking alternatives article]
 
 
  ¹ Comparison vs. cigarette smoking, based on sensory testing comparing odor intensity in air after generation of smoke of Winston Blue cigarette and vapor from Ploom X (Rich, Fresh and Berry Fresh). The testing were performed with a panel of 12 assessors by external laboratory in Germany. All panel members are selected and trained according to DIN EN 13725:2003.

QUESTIONS: Do tobacco sticks produce tar?
ANSWERS:
No. Heated tobacco is different from burning tobacco.
 
 Using HeatFlow Tobacco Heating Technology, the stick is heated from the outside to the core, gently releasing rich tobacco flavor throughout the session. 
 
 HeatFlow Innovative HT technology doesn't produce the tar that's generated by burning tobacco, which means there's no smoke and less tobacco smell on your clothes, hair and breath¹, and less visible staining on your teeth, when compared with smoking².
 
 ¹ Comparison vs. cigarette smoking, based on sensory testing comparing odor intensity on human hair/100% cotton exposed to smoke of Winston Blue cigarette and vapor from Ploom X (rich, fresh and berry fresh). The testing were performed with a panel of 12 assessors by external laboratory in Germany. All panel members are selected and trained according to DIN EN 13725:2003.
 ² Comparison vs. cigarette after use, based on color comparison of teeth exposed to smoke of Standard reference cigarette (1R6F) and vapor from Ploom X (Rich, Fresh and Berry Fresh). Exposure was conducted in our internal laboratory and color measurement was conducted by external laboratory in Japan. Bovine teeth were used for this study with reference to ISO 28399.

QUESTIONS: When should I replace my tobacco stick?
ANSWERS:
One tobacco stick will last for one session, and you shouldn't re-use a tobacco stick. 
  
  Once you've ended the session, your Ploom device will turn itself off (you'll know this is happening because you'll feel a long vibration and see the lights turn off). Take out your used tobacco stick carefully - it might be hot straight after you've used it. You can leave it in a stick tray until it cools down, and then put it in the bin. 
  
  To find out more about replacing your tobacco stick, watch our video. [Link to How to Ploom video]

QUESTIONS: How long does a session last?
ANSWERS:
Your session length depends on which device you have and which heating mode you chose. 
  
  If you've got a Ploom S, in Standard Mode your session will last 4 minutes and 30 seconds. And in Intense Mode, it'll last for 4 minutes. You can take as many puffs as you want - the number won't affect the length of your session. 
  
  Ploom X only has one heating mode. Your session will last for 5 minutes. And if you're wondering how many puffs you can take with Ploom X, you can take as many as you want.

QUESTIONS: If a stick breaks and gets stuck, how do I get it out?
ANSWERS:
​If a part of your tobacco stick gets stuck in the heating chamber, here's what to do:
  
  Turn your Ploom device off and wait for it to cool down. Once it has cooled, grab a pair of non-metallic tweezers and take the stick out. It's really important that you use non-metallic tweezers as using metal could be dangerous. Make sure you remove the stick as carefully as possible, so you don't scratch or damage the inside of the heating chamber.

QUESTIONS: Do Ploom points expire?
ANSWERS:

 It's a good idea to check at the end of each calendar year to see if you've got any points that are due to expire, and see what your membership level is.

QUESTIONS: Can I transfer my Ploom points to a friend?
ANSWERS: No - you can't transfer your Ploom points to a friend.
text: Can I transfer my Ploom points to a friend? No - you can't transfer your Ploom points to a friend.

QUESTIONS: When I reach a certain Ploom Club status, is it for life?
ANSWERS:
No - Here's how it works:
 
 When you earn enough points to move to a higher status level, your status will be upgraded immediately upon earning those points.
 
 In your first year as a Ploom Club member, if you obtain a higher status level, you will keep it until the end of your second year.
 
 After that, your status will updated at the end of each calendar year.
 
 If you have collected enough points within that calendar year to retain a higher status level, it will remain unchanged until the end of the next calendar year. If you have not earned enough points within that calendar year to retain your status, you will be changed to the status level that you have earned enough points to qualify for. 
 
 Then, you can earn points [Insert link to Earn Points page] in a variety of ways to increase your balance and regain a higher status level.
